KonectIQ Development Roadmap

As we are in active Alpha development, this roadmap provides a high-level view of our priorities and planned features.

Phase 1: Alpha (Current Focus)

The primary goal of Alpha is establishing core technical hygiene checks and ensuring stable read-only cloud connectivity.

Feature Area

Target Completion

Details

Connectivity

Complete

Secure read-only integration with AWS.

SkyEdge™ Engine

80% Complete

Implementation of initial three cost-saving checks (Idle VM, Over-provisioned DB, Orphaned Storage).

Shield™ Security

50% Complete

Implementation of initial two security checks (Public S3/Storage Access, Unencrypted Volumes).

Dashboard

60% Complete

Core UI for viewing the Top 3 Fixes and estimated savings.

Phase 2: Beta (Next 3-6 Months)

Beta will focus on expanding cloud coverage and introducing more sophisticated analysis.

Multi-Cloud Expansion: Full read-only integration for Microsoft Azure resources.

Deeper Cost Analysis: Implement checks for load balancers without targets and auto-scaling groups with misconfigured minimum sizes.

Alerting System: Basic email/notification integration for high-risk findings.

User Management: Basic user profile and settings configuration via Firestore.

Phase 3: General Availability (TBD)

The goal for GA is a stable, reliable tool with broad coverage.

Full Multi-Cloud Support: Integration for Google Cloud Platform (GCP).

Reporting: Historical trend reports on cloud waste reduction over time.

Advanced Security: Checks for IAM roles with excessive permissions and rotation of access keys.

On-Premises Hybrid Support: Initial exploration of monitoring hybrid environments.
